    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-29T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-29T23:00:00-05:00" n="119"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6629: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-30T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >April 30, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 30—1:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. My 83, April 29, 7 p.m.<note n="80" xml:id="d119fn80">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_232">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 232</ref>.</note> Despite previous
                    announcement by the Foreign Office spokesman that an official statement
                    clarifying Japan’s policy in China would be issued this afternoon, Amau said at
                    the press conference this morning that no such statement would be issued and
                    that he considered the affair “a closed incident”. No mention was made of the
                    American <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    <note n="81" xml:id="d119fn81">See telegram No. 59, April 28, 7 p.m., to the
                        Ambassador in Japan, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_231">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 231</ref>.</note> presented to the
                    Minister by me last evening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
